20)What is the Difference Between Tree and Graph?
  ->A Tree is a special type of Graph that is hierarchical, connected, and contains no cycles.
  A Tree always has one root node and exactly one path between any two nodes.
  For n nodes, a Tree always contains n−1 edges.
  ->A Graph is a collection of vertices and edges that may contain cycles and multiple paths between nodes.
  Graphs do not require a root node and can represent complex relationships such as social networks and road maps.
  Every Tree is a Graph, but every Graph is not a Tree.

